-- South Korea Department Store Sales Rose 1.6% in March
-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 2012-04-18T21:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/south-korea-department-store-sales-rose-1-6-in-march.html
Sales at major South Korean
department stores rose for a second month as  consumer confidence 
and job market conditions improved.  Outlays at the three biggest chains rose 1.6 percent from a
year earlier in March after a 2.9 percent gain in February, the
Ministry of  Knowledge Economy  said in a statement today.
